    <sec id="sec19">
      <title>Coordinated annotation tracks</title>
      <p>Six user-friendly tracks are visualized with rapid response time. Coordinated annotation tracks are provided to show genome structure and key domains, allele frequencies, sequence similarity between various coronavirus, multi-genome alignment and primer sets for detection of SARS-CoV-2 (Figures S8–S11, see Supplemental Materials and Methods Section 10). The track-related data files are available via <ext-link xlink:href="https://ngdc.cncb.ac.cn/ncov/apis/data-latest/" ext-link-type="uri">https://ngdc.cncb.ac.cn/ncov/apis/data-latest/</ext-link>.</p>
    </sec>
    <sec id="sec20">
      <title>Transmission case studies through CGB</title>
      <p>Based on the large data volume and user-friendly CGB, many analyses can be quickly conducted. Take the spread of VOCs in India as an example. Among the <inline-formula><tex-math notation="LaTeX" id="ineq09">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
