    <p>We also found that the mutation rate could be different among sites. Using the CGB core data file, we conducted a 10-base sliding window analysis with a sliding step of one base and identified fine-scaled mutation cold spots along the viral genome (see Supplemental Materials and Methods Section 15), indicating the genomic regions with mutation rate significantly lower than the average mutation rate of the entire genome. In total, 657,074 (recurrent) mutations were identified and 868 mutation cold spots were found with a false discovery rate (FDR) corrected <italic toggle="yes">P</italic>-value <inline-formula><tex-math notation="LaTeX" id="ineq12">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
